This file describes features that are not yet implemented, and bugs that are not yet fixed.

* (done) Configuration management
  Implemented in lib/config.cpp: 3-tier config system
  (system /usr/local/etc/crate.yml, drop-in /usr/local/etc/crate.d/*.yml,
  user ~/.config/crate/crate.yml).

* (bug) net/inbound: crates can listen on any ports for inbound connections, but connections are rejected from the host itself.
  See bug#239590: ipfw rule doesn't forward TCP connections made through the host's LAN address

* (feature) Cross-device folder and file shares need to be implemented.

* (bug) pkg/add: command is not yet implemented (was calling abort(), now returns a proper error).

* (security) X11 shared mode provides no display isolation.
  Jail processes sharing the host X11 socket can read keystrokes and manipulate windows.
  Users should prefer mode=nested or mode=headless for security-sensitive workloads.

* (feature) SNMP AgentX: the AgentX wire protocol is not yet implemented (snmpd runs in stub mode).
